  (81, 123481, NULL, 'Toxic work environment', 1, 'Good location, decent salary', 'Terrible management, no work-life balance, high turnover rate', 'Full-time', 'Software Engineer', false, NULL, 'approved', '2025-01-30 18:03:26.24+00', '2025-03-16 18:03:26.338679+00'),
  (83, 123481, NULL, 'Avoid at all costs', 1, 'Learned what not to do in my career', 'Toxic culture, poor compensation, no growth opportunities', 'Full-time', 'Customer Support', false, NULL, 'approved', '2024-12-01 18:03:26.24+00', '2025-03-16 18:03:26.540654+00'),
  (85, 123482, NULL, 'Avoid at all costs', 1, 'Good location, nice office, nice coworkers.', 'Boss was highly unprofessional - demanding things "instantly", berating and insulting employees.  No benefits - I had to search for and pay for my own.   Employer timed bathroom breaks and lunches and deducted pay for extra bathroom time.  Constant insults and screaming.   Very stressful environment. ', NULL, 'Senior Administrative Assistant', false, 'Debbie Mayberry', 'pending', '2025-03-18 19:40:45.927836+00', '2025-03-18 19:40:45.927836+00'),
  (86, 123485, NULL, 'Owner''s Daughter Thinks She''s a Tyrannical God', 1, 'Scare acting is a lot of fun, get to scream at people, dress up in costumes. Saturdays they provide food fcfs style (pizza, goulash, tacos, nachos, etc.) right after closing to the actors.', 'Pay is minimum wage, management has no concerns for the well-being of their staff, and the owner''s daughter cares even less. Total disregard for safety, history of hiring known SOs and then placing them as actors in walk through attractions - sometimes working right alongside minors. Attractions themselves are falling apart, molding, and overall just a major electrical fire hazard. Speaking on the Saturday night food thing, good luck getting food, they don''t order enough for the entire staff, and some attractions that close up earlier have been known to pig out. Big Brother surveillance system to the max. Cameras everywhere, both inside and outside of attractions, and don''t say the wrong thing out of context around the wrong person, staff and management both openly encourages staff hazing and retaliation behavior. When problems are brought up, they''re usually addressed with a "but can you work it out?" or "just quit then" attitude.', NULL, 'Haunt Actor', false, '', 'pending', '2025-07-06 20:32:02.118844+00', '2025-07-06 20:32:02.118844+00'),
  (87, 123486, NULL, 'A very family, help the relative type of company', 1, 'The actual boss that he passed away a few years ago', 'Make the boss''s son in law become more human amd empathetic when he is an a**le. He brought the evaluation system and he is using it whenever he feels like. A donkey could have better judgment crisis than his and he is marketing the firm in a middle-east bazar style. He is not a fair person. He doesn''t have any idea what he is usually talking about and he will never ever replace his father in law. Not to say about his favoritism on some people in the firm that they are somehow connected, politically or by convenience to the point that is detrimental for people that work hard in the firm to prove their value. The guy needs real life lessons and stop acting that he cozyed up with the elite, just because he married the boss''s daughter.', NULL, 'Associate', false, '', 'pending', '2025-07-21 05:25:51.312453+00', '2025-07-21 05:25:51.312453+00'),
  (88, 123487, NULL, 'Sweat shop', 1, 'They will love you for 2 years then thrown you out once you start to get to expensive.  ', 'Toxic culture.  ', NULL, 'Consultant', false, '', 'pending', '2025-09-08 15:57:58.551064+00', '2025-09-08 15:57:58.551064+00'),
  (90, 123493, NULL, 'TOXIC AS IT GETS', 1, 'The teams themselves are really nice and great people. That''s the only pro', 'The management/owners always have to have someone to target and blame for issues. The "priority" changes every day so those in charge are always treated like they aren''t doing things correctly even though they are doing what they were told to do last. They treat people as replaceable. They give people more responsibility than anyone could handle then act surprised when things aren''t getting done and then tell you its because youre not efficient. They have fired someone while off for a funeral, told a pregnant women that if she cant work in 90 degrees when the AC wasnt working then she could just not come in, said they wouldnt recall anything unless people ended up in the hospital, they lie about the ingredients, and have the mentality of "let''s just do it until we get caught". Everyone felt like they were walking on eggshells as soon as the owners came in because they didn''t want to be the next target. DO NOT WORK HERE!', NULL, 'Multiple', false, '', 'pending', '2025-11-12 00:10:22.509825+00', '2025-11-12 00:10:22.509825+00'),
  (91, 123494, NULL, 'The most chaotic and unprofessional workplace I’ve ever encountered', 1, 'The only positive aspect was that some colleagues were genuinely supportive and kind. They did their best to help each other survive the chaos, even though management offered no structure or training.', 'Working at the Australian Institute of Entrepreneurship (AIE) was honestly one of the worst professional experiences I’ve ever had. The management is a complete mess — the people who interviewed and communicated with me before I joined were all fired within my first month. That alone says everything about how unstable and poorly run this place is.\n\nThere is zero training. Literally none. They hand you a random folder and expect you to magically understand everything on your own. It felt like they had no idea what they were doing and expected staff to just “figure it out.”\n\nThe school refuses to pay commissions to education agents but still expects you to “build strong agent relationships.” It’s impossible and completely dishonest. KPIs were changed without warning and tripled before the end of my probation — clearly designed to make sure no one ever meets them.\n\nOne manager even suggested that I “promote the school to random people on the train after work.” I wish I was joking. It was ', NULL, 'Marketing Manager', false, '', 'pending', '2025-11-13 04:08:30.370446+00', '2025-11-13 04:08:30.370446+00'),
  (92, 123495, NULL, 'I would not recommend ever working here', 1, '- Many employees are mission-driven and do good work to advance the mission', '- Dishonesty and lack of trust from leadership\n- Lack of support for professional development\n- Lack of job security or stability\n- Toxic workplace culture, especially among leadership\n- No accountability measures in place for management-level employees\n- Lower level employees treated with disrespect \n- Huge perceived conflict of interest with the Executive Board (e.g., The Executive Chair works for a large Internet Service Provider) that undermines the organization''s mission of achieving digital equity\n', NULL, 'Marketing Manager', false, '', 'pending', '2025-11-14 16:13:19.834697+00', '2025-11-14 16:13:19.834697+00'),
  (93, 123491, NULL, 'Effective and efficient team + impactful work ', 5, 'I enjoy working with Lever Foundation because of how efficient the system is and how everyone in the team is impact-driven. I get a lot of sovereignty and take ownership of my work; we are always trying to improve the efficacy of the work we do, which I highly appreciate.', 'If working remotely is not for you, this is not for you; you also need to have high self-discipline since we work independently most of the time.', NULL, 'Program Manager', true, '', 'pending', '2025-11-20 16:21:58.576907+00', '2025-11-20 16:21:58.576907+00'),
  (94, 123496, NULL, 'Work Culture', 1, 'Beautiful campus close to Niagara Falls', 'Leadership in the Master of Management program needs a lot of improvement. Unprofessional attitude, non-compliant with long-standing Canadian values for work culture, undermining the core of leadership, i.e., integrity and empathy. The culture is eroding the roots of the organization''s presence in Canada. ', NULL, 'Customer Support', false, '', 'pending', '2025-11-20 23:34:13.939773+00', '2025-11-20 23:34:13.939773+00') ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
